HEADWORD: Transmissive
<hw>Trans*mis"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Capable of
being transmitted; derived, or handed down, from one to
another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Itself a sun, it with <qex>transmissive</qex> light⟦br⟧
Enlivens worlds denied to human sight.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transmit</ent>⟦br⟧
